cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 65 miles WSW of St. Petersburg, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving north toward the west-central Florida coast, then forecast to turn northeast, cross the northern Florida peninsula, and emerge into the western Atlantic off the northeast Florida/Georgia coast
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near or just north of Cedar Key, FL (west-central Florida coast)

weather_observation.watch_coast: North of the Suwannee River to Aucilla River, FL (Big Bend area)
weather_observation.warning_coast: Bonita Beach to Suwannee River, FL including Tampa Bay and Charlotte Harbor
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Much of the Florida Peninsula, including the east-central coast from Melbourne/Port Canaveral northward to Jacksonville
weather_observation.wind: Tropical-storm-force winds (sustained 25–35 mph, gusts 40–50 mph) possible late Wednesday night through Thursday afternoon
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor surge of 1–2 ft possible along the east-central Florida coast including Port Canaveral at times of high tide
weather_observation.rainfall: 2–4 inches with localized totals up to 6 inches may produce ponding and localized flooding around the port
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous surf and rip currents; isolated tornado threat in rainbands
